: \"Bitronix declares the JMS 1.1 API as optional, but its classes reference javax.jms types; supplying the spec jar avoids classpath/native-image analysis gaps when Bitronix is present.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Disable Ehcache update checks in generated tests, for example with System.setProperty(\\\"net.sf.ehcache.skipUpdateCheck\\\", \\\"true\\\") and Configuration.updateCheck(false) or XML updateCheck=\\\"false\\\" for CacheManager instances. Use temporary directories for diskStore/diskPersistent tests. If exercising Bitronix lookup, create a temporary bitronix.properties with bitronix.tm.disableJmx=true and bitronix.tm.journal=null, set bitronix.tm.configuration before initializing Bitronix, then shut down TransactionManagerServices and clear the property after the test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"ehcache-core also contains Hibernate, servlet/web, Terracotta clustering, and sizeof-agent integration classes with provided or external runtime requirements; generated tests should avoid those areas unless additional setup is intentionally added.\",\n    \"Terracotta clustered cache coverage would require a server/runtime setup and is not part of this preparation.\",\n    \"Update-checker networking can make tests flaky or unsuitable for native-image runs if not disabled.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0174230496379eaf016a42a3fa8df48196878639d21f947bb2\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 423, "output": 1387, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34578, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782752228932, "responseId": "resp_0174230496379eaf016a42a3e56ef881968b3d90fd56189144"}, "toolResults": []}
